# Master Rewrite Prompt: Property Empire (Offline Edition)
Role: You are an expert Full-Stack React Developer specializing in MapLibre GL, TypeScript, and Local State Management.

Objective: Rewrite the "Property Empire" application from a Firebase-multiplayer game to a Local-First Single-Player game. You must maintain a 1:1 visual match of the UI, animations, and economy logic while implementing a Simulated Bot Economy.

## 1. Core Architecture & State Migration
Replace all Firebase/Firestore dependencies with a unified local state (e.g., Zustand or React Context + LocalStorage).  
+2

Player State: Initialize with $1,000,000 cash, $1,000,000 net worth, and Level 1 (5 XP).  

Database Simulation: Instead of Firestore, maintain a local object containing users (Player + 10-20 generated Bots), properties, and listings.  
+2

Data Loading: Retain the dataManager logic using idb-keyval to fetch and cache the 100MB world property dataset from GitHub.  
+1

## 2. Visual & Map Specifications
Replicate the MapLibre GL environment exactly:

Projection: Use the 3D Globe projection.  

Layering: Implement the properties-layer symbol layer with zoom-based visibility (minZoom/maxZoom) and priority sorting defined in GAME_CONFIG.ts.  
+1

Interactive Popups: Use the custom-property-popup CSS class to render the PropertyPopupContent with a transparent, blurred background, ignoring default MapLibre styling.  
+1

HUD: Keep the top-left asset trackers and the bottom-right action column (Map Filter, News, Marketplace, Leaderboard, Portfolio, Dashboard).  

## 3. Automated Economic Engines
Migrate the hourly engines to run on a local timer:

Volatility Engine: Every game-hour, shift the baseValue of all global properties by a random percentage (-5% to +5%) and update the 20-tick history for the LivePortfolio graphs.  
+1

Rent Engine: Every game-hour, calculate dividends for the player and all bots based on their ownership percentage of property categories (e.g., Country, City, Landmark).  
+1

Simulated Bot Engine (New): Create a background service where bots:

Buy available shares from the bank.  
+1

Post shares on the Marketplace for random asking prices.  

Place bids on player listings.  
+1

Send direct P2P offers to the player via the NewsModal.  
+1

## 4. Feature Parity Requirements
Ensure these features are implemented 1:1 with the original logic:

Marketplace: A global auction house showing player and bot listings. Implement the Escrow bidding logic where outbid players/bots are immediately refunded.  
+1

Executive Dashboard: Portfolio management for selling shares back to the bank or listing them for sale.  

Direct Offers: Allow players to send offers to bots (visible in the "Current Shareholders" list) and receive offers from bots in the NewsModal.  
+2

Global Leaderboard: Rank the player against the simulated bots based on total Net Worth.  

Live Portfolio: Real-time Chart.js graphs tracking asset performance with PnL percentages.  

## 5. Technical Constraints
Styling: Use Tailwind CSS and the specific configurations from index.css and App.css.  
+1

Modularity: Keep the code modular; do not combine hooks like useBuyProperty or useMarketplace into a single file.  
+1

Config Rigidity: Strictly follow the GAME_CONFIG.ts values for baseShares, hourlyIncome, and xpMultiplier.  

Instruction: Begin by setting up the local state provider and the dataManager before building out the Map.tsx and Hud.tsx components.
